A minimalistic illustration of a single pristine white sheet of paper floating in an infinite pale gray void, with three translucent rectangular cutout shapes hovering just above it like ghostly stencils casting soft shadows. The cutouts suggest different interface layouts - one with horizontal lines like a form, one with a grid pattern like a list, one with circular and rectangular shapes like a login. Delicate dotted lines connect the floating stencils to the paper below, suggesting they can be placed down when needed. The composition is clean, airy, and architectural, with subtle gradients and a sense of potential and modularity. No text, no icons, just pure geometric shapes implying structure and choice.
